Job Description:
• Performs head office and branch audits in accordance with the internal audit programs and procedures including identifying and defining issues, developing criteria, reviewing and analyzing evidences and documenting the head office and branch or department control process under the supervision of Senior Auditors and Team Leader;

• Conducts interviews, reviews documents, develops and administers surveys, composes summary memos, and prepares working papers in current audit files;

• Update audit programs and audit check lists;

• Documents the findings/issues, drafts the recommendations using independent judgments, and submits the draft to Senior Auditor and Team Leader for review in a timely manner;

• Builds and maintain respectful and effective communication and relationship with teams, managements and staff of areas under review;

• Maintains confidentiality of bank and customer affairs in accordance with standards of professional conduct of auditors;

• Ensure that recommendations are clearly presented to and agreed to by management and that a subsequent audit report will be issued promptly;

• Ensure that all agreed upon recommendations are subsequently implemented;

• Performs related work as assigned by seniors, Team Leaders and Managers.

Job Requirement:
• Bachelor degree in auditing, accounting or others related fields;

• Knowledge of IT audit is encouraged to apply;

• Very good in English for both writing and speaking;

• Ability to work in team;

• Fast learner , commitment, flexible and responsible;

• Self-starter and self-motivator;

• Good English proficiency, both written and spoken;

• Dynamics and good interpersonal skill.

***Interested applicants meeting the above requirements should submit their CV along with a cover letter to recruitment@cambodiapostbank.com no later than December 28, 2014 

